## Preparing for the Worst

If someone forgets to pass an argument, having `undefined` usually breaks things! (E.g., `Hello undefined!`).

You can set a **Default Parameter** by using the `=` sign when defining the function.

```javascript
// If no name is provided, default to 'Guest'
function greetUser(name = "Guest") {
  console.log("Hello " + name);
}

greetUser("Sarah"); // Prints: Hello Sarah
greetUser();        // Prints: Hello Guest
```
